<SLUG> BC-BKN-SUNS-KJ-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KJ WON'T PLAY THIS SEASON  
 ALSO DOUBTFUL ABOUT NEXT YEAR 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By NORM FRAUENHEIM  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Kevin Johnson returned to an NBA playing floor on
Sunday, but not as a player. He was there to honor the past.
</P>
<P>
   The future will have to wait.
</P>
<P>
   After a ceremony honoring a former teammate, Tom Chambers, KJ
said he wouldn't sign with a playoff team. The former Suns guard
also expressed doubts about next year.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not going to play this season,'' KJ said after Chambers'
name was added to a ring of honor at halftime of a 99-93, Suns'
victory over the Seattle at America West Arena.
</P>
<P>
   About next season, KJ said: ``I don't think I'm going to play,
but I'm not going to rule it out until after the summer. I'll
evaluate it then.''
</P>
<P>
   Unlike Dennis Rodman, KJ is still eligible to join a roster.
Rodman is ineligible. The Los Angeles Lakers cut him Thursday, long
after an NBA-imposed deadline.
</P>
<P>
   A free agent released after midnight, March 18 is prohibited
from signing with another team. The rule is intended to prevent
teams out of the playoffs from helping contenders in exchange for
some sort of under-the-table compensation.
</P>
<P>
   KJ, 33, looked as fit as he had in any of his 11 seasons with
the Suns. Could he play if he had a sudden change of heart?
</P>
<P>
   ``Of course,'' said the former playmaker, who is the franchise's
all-time leader in assists. ``My body's better than it's ever been.
I can walk up stairs and it doesn't hurt. I feel great.''
</P>
<P>
   KJ said he was approached by teams before and after the season
began in February.
</P>
<P>
   ``I told everybody no,'' he said. ``Every team called _ the
Lakers right off the bat.''
</P>
<P>
   He said loyalty to the Suns makes it difficult for him to play
elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's hard for me to put on another uniform,'' he said. ``Iknew
that all along. I knew when I stepped down from here that it would
be almost impossible for me to play anywhere else.''
</P>
<P>
   Chances are remote that he would ever put on a Suns' uniform
again. He and management agreed last spring to go separate ways.
</P>
<P>
   In their first season without KJ, the Suns have struggled. With
only nine games left in regular-season, they are only one game
above .500. KJ has watched from afar.
</P>
<P>
   ``How could I not?'' said KJ, who continues to work with
underprivileged kids. ``This team was such a big part of my life
for so long. There are a lot different players and pieces. But it's
happening. They'll be all right.
</P>
<P>
   KJ, who was accompanied by former Philadelphia 76ers great and
current Orlando executive Julius Erving, said ``I miss teammates I
miss the fans. This has been my life since I was 13-14 years old.
You know, 20 years. There's nothing like NBA basketball. That was a
great period. I appreciate what I had.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
