<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-DRAFT-GRADES-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TRADE EARNS REDSKINS TOP GRADE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   New Orleans Saints Coach Mike Ditka showed up in dreadlocks
Sunday and then promised teams would dread playing against Texas
running back Ricky Williams.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're going to the Super Bowl,'' Ditka said. ``We got the
final piece of the puzzle.''
</P>
<P>
   Saints fans better enjoy Williams, the Heisman Trophy winner who
wears his hair in dreadlocks. He cost them the rest of this year's
draft and two high picks next year in a trade with Washington,
which is why they get a grade of B, for bizarre.
</P>
<P>
   Many in the NFL think Ditka has lost in his mind in making the
trade.
</P>
<P>
   Williams isn't one of them, but he acknowledged that he thought
Ditka was ``crazy'' for wearing the dreadlocks wig.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm jealous,'' Williams said. ``It's longer than mine.''
</P>
<P>
   Here's a look at the rest of the draft grades:
</P>
<P>
   NFC East
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Redskins _ Champ Bailey with the seventh pick overall? It's one
of the all-time steals. Three No. 1 picks next year is unheard of.
Grade: A+.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Cardinals _ Here's what ``Sports Illustrated's'' Peter King
wrote about their draft: ``I think you can't underestimate what a
good job Arizona did in the first round. To get two starting
players _ Ohio State wide receiver David Boston and tackle L.J.
Shelton _ in one draft is rare. Grade: A-.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Cowboys _ They had to find a replacement for Leon Lett, and
North Carolina's Ebenezer Ekuban has a chance to be the guy. Grade:
B.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Eagles _ Former option quarterbacks shouldn't be taken second
overall. It's understandable that Eagles fans booed. Grade: C+.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Giants _ Second-round pick Joe Montgomery was just a part-time
starter and damaged goods. Grade: D+.
</P>
<P>
   NFC Central
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Bears _ They wanted UCLA quarterback Cade McNown and got him
and five extra picks. Brilliance and Bears haven't been mentioned
in the same sentence in years. Grade: A.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Lions _ Getting Southern California middle linebacker Chris
Claiborne ninth overall was a gift from the heavens. Grade: A-.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Buccaneers _ Lining up Louisiana State defensive tackle Anthony
McFarland next to Warren Sapp will be scary for offenses. Grade:
B+.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Packers _ Filled pressing needs in the secondary by saturating
the position. Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Vikings _ How do you draft a player (Michigan State's Dimitrius
Underwood) in the first round who didn't play last year because of
discipline reasons? Grade: C-.
</P>
<P>
   NFC West
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Rams _ The Rams might not have a quarterback, but they have
weapons in North Carolina State wide receiver Torry Holt and
running back Marshall Faulk, acquired from Indianapolis. Grade: A.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Falcons _ They ruined a good draft by trading away next year's
No. 1. Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Saints _ Never before has a team had only one pick in a draft.
They could have gone fishing Sunday. Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Panthers _ They sat out the first round but rebounded nicely
with Georgia offensive tackle Chris Terry. Grade: C+.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; 49ers _ Bill Walsh said he would take a quarterback and didn't.
That wasn't genius-like. Grade: C.
</P>
<P>
   AFC East
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Bills _ As always, they made few draft mistakes and filled
needs, especially at cornerback with Ohio State's Antoine
Wingfield. Grade: B+.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Dolphins _ How many running backs can play at the same time?
Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Patriots _ They wanted Miami running back Edgerrin James and
settled for LSU's Kevin Faulk in the second round. Grade: B-.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Colts _ James might turn out to be a good player, but he wasn't
worth the third pick in the draft. Rebounded nicely in later
rounds. Grade: B-.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Jets _ Only the diehard Jets fans can get excited about getting
guards. Grade: C-.
</P>
<P>
   AFC Central &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Browns _ They didn't fill a need at running back but addressed
all others, and most picks were solid. They got first-round value
in getting Syracuse wide receiver Kevin Johnson. Grade: A-.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Jaguars _ Defensive help is on its way, but it might not be
enough to catch Denver. Grade: B+.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Ravens _ They fell in love with University of Arizona players,
and rightfully so. Chris McAlister will upgrade their secondary
tremendously. Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Steelers _ Wide receiver Troy Edwards was a stretch at 13, but
he filled their top need. Grade: B-.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Bengals _ Akili Smith might be the best of the quarterbacks
taken at the top of the draft. Reached for players later. Grade:
B-.
</P>
<P>
   AFC West
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Seahawks _ Mike Holmgren did his best Jimmy Johnson imitation
by trading down, and it worked. Love the pick of Washington
quarterback Brock Huard in the third round. Grade: A-.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Chiefs _ To get the best offensive tackle in the draft with the
14th pick is more than just luck. Grade: A-.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Broncos _ What does a team that has almost everything need?
Depth, and the Broncos got it. Solid but not flashy. Grade: B-.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Raiders _ They must be trying to stockpile offensive tackles.
Grade: C.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Chargers _ School of choice goes from South Carolina State to
South Dakota State. Grade: C-.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
