<SLUG> BC-WORKWEEK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THIS WEEK'S TOO BUSY TO GET ANY REAL WORK DONE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By JONATHAN SIDENER  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Let's proclaim today (MONDAY) Try-to-Get-Some-Real &QL; 
-Work-Done Day.
</P>
<P>
   First of all, it needs to be adopted, proclaimed or otherwise
sponsored to fit in with the rest of the week. From bringing
daughters to work to honoring secretaries, almost every day this
week has been monikered for some cause. And Thursday has two.
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday is Telework Greater Phoenix Day, which means we all
should be home wearing bathrobes as we type and handle the phones.
Razor stubble is mandatory for men. Makeup is banned for women.
</P>
<P>
   Chances are you've seen those studies saying telecommuting
increases productivity. Well, here's a little-known fact: All that
research was underwritten by America Online, the Golf Channel and
the Association of American Doctors Advocating Frequent Napping.
</P>
<P>
   So forget about getting anything done Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday is Professional Secretaries Day. Prepare for a long
line when you stop at the florist on your way to work. You'll get
to your desk an hour and a half late, barely in time to get a lunch
reservation. So write off 2{ hours for lunch. By the time you get
back to the office, you'll barely have time to answer Tuesday's
e-mail. And of course, none of the Phoenix area's secretaries will
do a lick of work, further slowing our economic engine. The only
things staving off recession will be the record earnings reported
by florists and restaurants.
</P>
<P>
   Thursday is Take Our Daughters to Work Day. Bring little Suzy to
work. Spend the morning introducing her to your co-workers, showing
her the water cooler and bathroom. Show her your computer and watch
her delete that spreadsheet you've been building for the past seven
weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Those of us who have only sons or dogs will watch and know
you're not getting anything done. Out of resentment, we'll surf the
Internet and make long-distance calls to friends in Alaska.
</P>
<P>
   And if Take Our Daughters to Work Day isn't enough to send half
our businesses filing for Chapter 7, Thursday is also Earth Day. We
can't throw away any of the day's junk mail. We'll have to find
someplace to recycle it. Can't drive, either; that would waste gas.
We'll be walking around town with junk mail in one hand and an
empty diet soda can in the other.
</P>
<P>
   Friday, as always, is Casual Day. So far, it doesn't have any
other name. Maybe it'll end up as Bosses' Revenge Day. Or
Nobody-Goes-Home-Until-We're-Caught-Up Day.
</P>
<P>
   Gov. Jane Hull's office said there are no plans to proclaim
Friday as anything special. Similarly, a spokesman for Phoenix
Mayor Skip Rimsza said the mayor is not scheduled to rename Friday.
But whether or not any work gets done, Friday will have a special
description for the city's employees, spokesman Scott Phelps said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Friday will be payday,'' Phelps said. ``You can't beat
that.'' &QL; 
Jonathan Sidener can be reached at (602) 444-8169 or at
jon.sidener(at)pni.com via e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-19-99 0155EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
