</P>
<P>
   But in trade, nothing's bulletproof. American textile makers
will never like a deal that lets China expand its presence in the
American market. Nor will steel makers, or steel unions. Many in
Congress argue that China has no intention of fulfilling its
market-opening promises. But the vast majority of big businesses
say that if Clinton doesn't sign soon, the huge gains made in many
areas will be eaten away as soon as Zhu returns to Beijing and
