anonymous, open nature of the Net than to the writing skills of
Heather's creator.
</P>
<P>
   Whether ``gina'' was successful as a work of writing doesn't
matter; the experiment, at least for me, succeeded because readers
began to care for these characters, following their lives, sharing
their dreams and disappointments. The fictional adventures of
Heather and Gina became an experience for this audience. And,
because it was supposed to be real, even a casual reader could
write in and affect the outcome _ which they did. The immediate and
often very frank feedback shaped the story and the writing as it
continued.
</P>
<P>
   The Internet has become a place where those who want attention
can set up cameras in their home and broadcast their lives to the
