<HEADLINE>
NEW OVEN WILL DOUBLE YOUR COOKING PLEASURE
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.) 
 By FRANCES INGRAHAM  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. _ Cooking convenience is the name of the game for
busy families, especially in kitchens without much space.
</P>
<P>
   But it can be frustrating when trying to cook several dishes at
different temperatures in one oven, particularly for those who shun
microwaves or who don't own a toaster oven.
</P>
<P>
   To address this dilemma, Maytag Appliances has come up with one
solution that will be available at retail stores in July.
</P>
<P>
   It's an electric range with two ovens, allowing cooks to prepare
different menu items simultaneously at different times and
temperatures. It provides similar benefits to a double-wall oven
without the expense and hassle of remodeling.
</P>
<P>
   Called the Gemini range, it takes its name from the zodiac sign
of the twins and has one oven to accommodate large items such as a
Thanksgiving turkey and a smaller oven above it that heats up twice
as quickly to bake, broil, warm and toast with accuracy.
</P>
<P>
   Together, the two ovens provide a full 5.2 cubic feet of
capacity in the same space as a conventional freestanding range.
</P>
<P>
   The smaller oven, which can be used for food ranging from baked
potatoes to mini-pizzas, as well as heating rolls or keeping foods
and dishes warm, has an autoset temperature of 170. There's also a
scrolling control that gives automatic prompts when entering
cooking commands and allows the customization of clock options,
such as reminder beeps when baking time is completed.
</P>
<P>
   Priced at $1,399, the Gemini twin-oven range is scheduled to be
available in three colors _ white, black and a brushed chrome
finish.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-19-99 1204EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
