   BOOK-GROUND (Undated) _ Undeterred by having a galaxy's worth of
history to draw from, Salman Rushdie has used a tale of Orpheus
Descending to roam tragedy, mass culture and celebrity, global
politics, photography and comparative religion. By Gail Caldwell.
1395 words.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-LOOP (Undated) _ Michael Malone's book reminds us that
Apple's creators and leaders are as greedy and domineering as
Microsoft's _ just not as good at it. By Hiawatha Bray.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-TIPS (Undated) _ What's hot on the just-published list.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-POP (Boston) _ The national pop music scene is in as much
chaos as ever, from company consolidation to MP3 technology. By
Joan Anderman. 1800 words.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-MACHOVER (Undated) _ Tod Machover, from MIT's Media Lab,
talks about his new opera that will debut in Houston. By Richard
Dyer. 1750 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-MATRIX (Undated) _ While the storyline isn't great, the
cutting-edge special effects are. A talk with the creator. By Jim
Sullivan. 1600 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-GUIDE (Undated) _ Globe critics review current movies.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-VIDEOS (Undated) _ Good and bad in video films. By Globe
staff.
</P>
<P>
   STAGE-DUNCAN (Undated) _ Sandy Duncan is an unlikely ``bad
