   ROYCOM (Kansas City, Mo.) _ How does the name Kauffman Stadium
at Sprint Park grab you?
</P>
<P>
   Miles Prentice is exploring the many commercial possibilities
that go hand-in-hand with being the Royals owner. Prentice, who is
still seeking ownership approval by Major League Baseball, says
he's already discussed the idea of selling Kauffman Stadium naming
rights to the highest bidder.
</P>
<P>
   The question is, where would that money go _ to Prentice and the
Royals or to Jackson County? That's unclear for now, but at the
very least, Prentice plans to increase billboard advertising at the
stadium. Both dugouts, outfield walls and other areas within the
complex could all become marketing tools and sources of new
revenue. Story by Steve Rock. (Sports desk) Story will move in the
