<HEADER>
A4180 &Cx1f; taf-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  AM-NYT-BUDGET &LR;      04-19 1474
</HEADER>
<BODY>
 AM-NYT-BUDGET  
(gm) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; FOR TUESDAY AMs &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Here are today's top news stories from The New York Times News
Service for AMs of Tuesday, April 13:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; KOSOVO &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Brussels) _ NATO gives a briefing on the convoy
incident, with video; saying NATO forces may have killed the
civilians. NATO also blames the Yugoslav Army for having military
vehicles mixed with civilian vehicles. By Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-PILOTS (Washington) _ Peering down at the ground from
15,000 feet or higher, NATO pilots like those who apparently
attacked civilians in Kosovo by mistake rely on a combination of
technology and their own eyesight to identify what they are seeing.
By Richard W. Stevenson.
</P>
<P>
