earnings that sharply exceed Wall Street forecasts. First-quarter
profit was more than any other financial services company, and
exceeded the most recent profits of Microsoft, General Motors and
General Electric Co. Earnings rose 9 percent, to $2.36 billion, or
$1.01 share, surpassing forecasts of 87 cents a share. Bank of
America also posts earnings above estimates. By Timothy L. O'Brien.
