</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE FIRST AMERICANS: ORIGINS OF MAN &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FOUR COLOR SLIDES ARE AVAILABLE FREE &QL; 
 &UR; 1,000 words &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Exciting new evidence suggests that the first humans in the New
World were not, as previously believed, mammoth hunters from
Siberia who crossed the Bering Strait at the end of the Ice Age.
Who, when, where and how the first North Americans came to the
continent is an evolving mystery with some new, compelling and
evolving answers. The surprising remains of Spirit Cave in a museum
laboratory outside Carson City, Nev., offer startling clues about
the origins of mankind.
</P>
