<P>
   &UR; CONFLICT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA (Washington) _ At least 100,000 -- possibly as many
as 500,000 -- Kosovo Albanian men are unaccounted for, raising
fears that they may have been killed by Serb forces, US officials
say. By Bob Hohler and Anne E. Kornblut. 1300 words.
</P>
<P>
   NATO-SPIN (London) _ While Europe's most prominent spin doctor
worked to fix NATO's inexperienced public relations arm, the
alliance brings forth the commander leading the air war to admit
that his pilots may have killed refugees by mistake. By Kevin
Cullen. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   BALKANS-COSTS (Washington) _ President Clinton asks Congress for
$6 billion in emergency funds to pay for the war in Yugoslavia
until September. By Fred Kaplan. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA-MONTENEGRO (Podgorica, Yugoslavia) _ Slobodan
Milosevic orders the arrest of Montenegro's deputy prime minister,
who has said his countrymen should not be forced to fight in
Kosovo. By Susan Milligan. 1300 words.
</P>
