<SLUG> BC-CARSEAT-BEST-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CRASH-TEST FAVORITES
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies CAR SEAT WARS) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Consumer Reports recently crash-tested 28 child car seats to
come up with a list of favorites.
</P>
<P>
   The magazine of Consumers' Union asked an outside lab to perform
crash tests similar to the government's, strapping dummies of
various sizes into seats placed on a ring that was run through a
simulated head-on collision.
</P>
<P>
   Consumer researchers also judged how easy each seat was to use
and whether it could be installed correctly in vehicles with
different safety-seat systems and seat configurations.
</P>
<P>
   Top choices from their January 1999 report include:
</P>
<P>
   Infant seats: These are placed in a rear-facing position and are
for babies up to 20-22 pounds. They also double as infant carriers.
The top pick, the Graco 7497 LiteRider All-Terrain Travel System,
$160, comes with a stroller. Other top performers include the
Evenflo on My Way 207, $55, Century SmartFit Plus 4529, $60, and
Kolcraft Secura 43834, $60.
</P>
<P>
   Convertible seats: These work two ways _ rear-facing for babies
weighing up to 22 pounds and forward-facing for toddlers up to 40
pounds. Top-rated models include the Century 1000 STE Classic 4161,
$50, the Century 2000 STE Classic 4261, $60, and the Century 3000
Room-to-Grow Classic 4331, $70.
</P>
<P>
   Booster seats: These raise a child who weighs 30 to 60 pounds
high enough so he or she can use the vehicle's safety belt.
Top-rated picks: the Fisher-Price Safe Embrace 79750, $60, the
Evenflo Right Fit 245, $25 _ a CR ``Best Buy'' _ and the Kolcraft
Prodigy 53000, $50.
</P>
<P>
   Toddler/booster seats: These are used with a harness to secure
toddlers who weigh at least 20 to 30 pounds and without one when
the child weighs 40 pounds and can use the vehicle's seat belt.
Top-rated picks: the Cosco High Back Booster 02-442, $40, and the
Century Next Step 4920, $100.
</P>
<P>
   Consumer Reports' top picks for car seats can be found online at
www.consumerreports.org.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
