<P>
   CITIGROUP-EARNINGS (Undated) _ Citigroup, displaying the kind of
raw earnings power promised by the merger that created the
financial services giant last year, said Monday that first-quarter
profits jumped 9 percent, surpassing analysts' estimates and
earnings posted by such well-known titans as General Electric Co.
and Microsoft Corp. By Timothy L. O'Brien.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Top display)
</P>
<P>
   EMPIRICAL-ECONOMISTS (Princeton, N.J.) _ No group in the
profession of economics is challenging accepted wisdom more
vigorously than empirical economists like Alan Krueger. But
Krueger, for one, does so rather cautiously, and there is a reason
for his hesitation: Abstract thinkers still dominate academic
economics with their explanations of how people and markets behave.
By Louis Uchitelle.
</P>
