   _  &UR; Bob Weider &LR;  was taken by ``the conspicuous placement of the
Bomb Disposal Unit, a big, clearly identified white van, and its
smaller, mobile explosion-container trailer, right next to Sproul
Hall. ... A nice recruiting touch.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Stephen Vincent  &LR; noted the juxtaposition of  &UR; Amy Tan &LR; 's talk
about the effect of ancestral ghosts on her novels, &LR;  and the
Cal-ROTC recruiting show, in which ROTC members in green camouflage
``took turns rappelling in great leaps and bounds down the wall''
of Wheeler Hall. In light of current events in the former
Yugoslavia, ``it was a somewhat creepy spectacle,'' writes Vincent.
</P>
