the administration at Yosemite is looking for two ``centennial
interpreters'' to play  &UR; David &LR;  and  &UR; Jennie (Mother) &LR; 
 &UR; Curry &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   The Currys, who were schoolteachers in Redwood City, founded
Camp Curry in Yosemite on June 1, 1899. He is remembered for
``stentorian'' _ ``generous in voice, generous in build'' _ shouts;
she is remembered as being ``attentive to guest and employee
needs.''
</P>
<P>
   David and Mother will stroll through Curry Village ``while in
costume and character,'' give daily tours, host evening programs
and organize children's activities. Candidates should fax their
qualifications to (209) 372-1135.cq &LR;
