<SLUG> BC-TEX-CLINTON-VISIT-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Security prepares for Clinton visit
 &HT;    By Dick Stanley
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ The Secret Service was preparing Monday for
President Clinton's planned visit to Austin on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton is expected to land at the new Austin-Bergstrom
International Airport at 10:45 a.m. He will make a short speech to
invited guests, tour the airport passenger terminal, then go have
lunch with members of the Democratic National Committee at the West
Austin home of Roy Spence, an old friend and political backer.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton will be in Austin about six hours, said Dave Wilkinson,
the special agent in charge of the Austin office of the Secret
Service. The Secret Service is working with the Austin Police
Department, the Travis County Sheriff's Office and the state
Department of Public Safety on security matters.
</P>
<P>
   Austin Mayor Kirk Watson, Texas Gov. George W. Bush and other
dignitaries, including the family of the late Congresswoman Barbara
Jordan, for whom the airport's passenger terminal is named, are
expected to greet Clinton at the airport.
</P>
<P>
   Construction at the airport is expected to be halted during the
president's arrival and departure at 4:40 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton is scheduled to fly on to Houston Wednesday for a supper
hosted by the Democratic National Committee.
</P>
<P>
   Dick Stanley writes for the Austin American-Statesman, Austin,
Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
