<P>
   (NYT27) NEW YORK -- April 19, 1999 -- MRSCLINTON, 4-19 --
Hillary Clinton speaking at the Boathouse in Central Park on
Monday. Presenting herself as a New Yorker in spirit and in
politics, Hillary Rodham Clinton began a two-day tour through
Manhattan and Long Island on Monday, praising the state's history
and culture as she expounded for the first time on why she might
want to be the senator from a state she has never called home. ``I
love New York,'' she says. ``I always have.'' (Ruby Washington/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) BUDAPEST, Hungary -- April 19, 1999 --
HOLBROOKE-CONFIRM, 4-19 -- Richard Holbrooke, President Clinton's
special envoy to Yugoslavia, walks along the banks of the Danube
River last month hours after arriving from Belgrade where he
unsuccessfully tried to pursuade Yugoslav leader Slobodan Milosevic
to accept a peace plan in Kosovo and avoid NATO air strikes. Senate
leaders and the State Department say they are close to a deal that
could rescue Holbrooke's long-delayed nomination to lead the
American delegation to the United Nations. (Edward Keating/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT25) MILWAUKEE -- April 19, 1999 -- WIS-WELFARE-3, 4-19 --
