<HEADLINE>
POCKETS, POCKETS EVERYWHERE 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Last year cargo pants were all the rage. This year's
versions are called utility pants, which include painters' and
carpenters' pants and any that have multiple pockets in odd places.
</P>
<P>
   Lord &AMP; Taylor has a variation from Laundry by Shelli Segal, with
straight legs and a detachable belt bag ($170), and four styles by
DKNY Jeans: survival pants with drawstring hems ($68), cropped
pants with a zippered pocket ($68), biker shorts ($64) and short
shorts ($48). There are also multipocketed shorts by CK Calvin
Klein Jeans ($48) and Lauren by Ralph Lauren ($50).
</P>
<P>
   At Saks Fifth Avenue, there are utility pants by Diesel Style
Lab ($139), utility sweat pants by D&AMP;G ($195) and cropped pants
with oversize pockets and drawstring bottoms by Hammett ($256).
</P>
<P>
   Maharishi's cropped pants, replete with zippered pockets,
D-rings and drawstrings, are $215 at Barneys New York. And
Laundry's carpenter pants are $148 at Neiman Marcus. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
